==================================================
CONTRACT FILTERING LOGIC
==================================================

The system should suppress:
- low-fit contracts
- unrealistic opportunities
- impossible qualification scenarios
- high-risk delivery contracts

unless explicitly requested by the user.

==================================================
DISCOVERY MODES
==================================================

The user should eventually be able to choose qualification aggressiveness.

==================================================
CONSERVATIVE MODE
==================================================

Show only:
- high-confidence matches
- highly executable contracts
- strong win probability

==================================================
GROWTH MODE
==================================================

Include:
- moderate stretch opportunities
- strategically beneficial opportunities
- adjacent capability contracts

==================================================
AGGRESSIVE MODE
==================================================

Include:
- subcontract opportunities
- teaming opportunities
- ambitious stretch contracts
- relationship-building contracts

==================================================
SUBCONTRACTING INTELLIGENCE
==================================================

The platform should identify:
- contracts unsuitable for prime pursuit
- contracts suitable for subcontract participation
- likely areas where the user could contribute specialized expertise

EXAMPLES:
- XR subsystem contribution
- visualization support
- AI workflow support
- dashboard development
- simulation engineering

OUTPUT EXAMPLE:

{
  "recommended_strategy": "Subcontractor",
  "prime_bid_recommended": false,
  "possible_fit_areas": [
    "XR visualization",
    "Simulation tooling",
    "Interactive systems"
  ]
}

==================================================
PAST PERFORMANCE GAP ANALYSIS
==================================================

The platform should detect:
- missing certifications
- missing contract history
- required domain experience gaps
- operational maturity gaps

EXAMPLES:
- Tanker simulator experience required
- Overseas support required
- Existing federal contract vehicle participation required

OUTPUT:
Gap Analysis Report

==================================================
OPPORTUNITY SUPPRESSION SYSTEM
==================================================

If opportunity mismatch is severe:
the system should suppress the contract entirely by default.

EXAMPLES:
- company too small
- unsupported clearance requirements
- impossible staffing scale
- irrelevant technical scope
- unrelated industry category

